rule.Name: AvoidCodeDuplicatedInSameClassRule
rule.problem: There is similar code in various methods in the same class. Your code will be better if you can unify them.
rule.solution: You should apply the Extract Method refactoring and have a single implementation of the code.

rule.Name: AvoidCodeDuplicatedInSiblingClassesRule
rule.problem: There is similar code in various methods in sibling classes. Your code will be better if you can unify them.
rule.solution: You can apply the Pull Up Method refactoring.

rule.Name: AvoidComplexMethodsRule
rule.problem: Methods with a large cyclomatic complexity are hard to understand and maintain.
rule.solution: Simplify the method using refactors like Extract Method.

rule.Name: AvoidLackOfCohesionOfMethodsRule
rule.problem: The methods in this class lack cohesion (a higher score is better). This leads to code which is harder to understand and maintain.
rule.solution: You can apply the Extract Class or Extract Subclass refactoring.

rule.Name: AvoidLargeClassesRule
rule.problem: The class is trying to do too much. Generally if a class is too large, duplicated code will not be far away.
rule.solution: You can apply the Extract Class or Extract Subclass refactoring.

rule.Name: AvoidLongMethodsRule
rule.problem: Long methods are usually hard to understand and maintain. This method can cause problems because it contains more code than the maximum allowed.
rule.solution: You should apply an Extract Method refactoring, but there are other solutions.

rule.Name: AvoidLongParameterListsRule
rule.problem: Generally, long parameter lists are hard to understand because they become hard to use and inconsistent. And you will be forever changing them if you need more data.
rule.solution: You should apply the Replace parameter with method refactoring, or preserve whole object or introduce parameter object

rule.Name: AvoidNonAlphanumericIdentifierRule
rule.problem: This namespace, type or member name contains underscore(s).
rule.solution: Remove the underscore from the specified name.

rule.Name: AvoidRedundancyInTypeNameRule
rule.problem: This type name is prefixed with the last component of its enclosing namespace. This usually makes an API more verbose and less autocompletion-friendly than necessary.
rule.solution: Remove the prefix from the type or replace it with a more meaningful term in the context of the namespace.

rule.Name: AvoidReturningArraysOnPropertiesRule
rule.problem: By convention properties should not return arrays.
rule.solution: Return a read-only collection or replace the property by a method and return a copy of the array.

rule.Name: AvoidSpeculativeGeneralityRule
rule.problem: If you will need the feature in the future then you should implement it in the future.
rule.solution: You can apply various refactorings: Collapse Hierarchy, Inline Class, Remove Parameter or Rename Method.

rule.Name: CompareWithEmptyStringEfficientlyRule
rule.problem: This method compares a string with an empty string by using the Equals method or the equality (==) or inequality (!=) operators.
rule.solution: Compare String.Length with 0 instead. The string length is known and it's faster to compare integers than to compare strings.
